@startuml class_diagram_error_logging

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Calculator {
    .. Arithmetic ..
    + add(a, b)
    + subtract(a, b)
    + multiply(a, b)
    + divide(a, b)
    .. Power & Logarithm ..
    + power(base, exponent)
    + square_root(x)
    + ln(x)
    + log10(x)
    .. Special ..
    + modulo(a, b)
    + absolute_value(x)
    + factorial(n)
    + is_prime(n)
    --
    raises: ValueError
    raises: ZeroDivisionError
}

class ErrorLog {
    .. Lazy init — file created on first log_error() call ..
    - _file_path: str
    --
    + __init__(file_path: str = "error_log.txt")
    + log_error(error_category: str, operation: str,\n  inputs: list, description: str)
    --
    error_categories: invalid_input | unsupported_operation\n               | calculation_error
    format: ISO8601_UTC | category | operation\n       | inputs_csv | description
    note: file I/O exceptions silently swallowed
}

class OperationHistory {
    .. Eager truncation — file cleared at __init__() ..
    - _file_path: str
    --
    + __init__(file_path: str = "history.txt")
    + add_entry(operation: str, inputs: list, result)
    --
    records: SUCCESSFUL operations only
    note: file I/O errors logged, not propagated
}

class "__main__" as main <<module>> {
    + cli_mode(args)
    + interactive_mode()
    - _parse_cli_arguments(args, error_log)
    - _execute_cli_mode(operation, operands, calc, error_log)
    - _run_interactive_loop(calc, error_log, history)
    - _parse_number(value: str) : float
}

database "error_log.txt" as error_file {
}

database "history.txt" as history_file {
}

main --> Calculator : instantiates
main --> ErrorLog : instantiates
main --> OperationHistory : instantiates (interactive only)

main ..> ErrorLog : passes error_log to\n_parse_cli_arguments()\n_execute_cli_mode()\n_run_interactive_loop()

main ..> OperationHistory : passes history to\n_run_interactive_loop() only\n(not used in CLI mode)

ErrorLog --> error_file : appends on first call\n(lazy init)
OperationHistory --> history_file : truncates at init,\nthen appends

Calculator -[hidden]right- ErrorLog
ErrorLog -[hidden]right- OperationHistory

note bottom of Calculator
  No dependency on ErrorLog
  or OperationHistory.
  Raises exceptions; caller
  decides how to handle them.
end note

@enduml
